President Biden has declared a major disaster in Nebraska due to severe storms and straight-line winds that occurred on May 12, 2022. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding is available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Andrew P. Meyer has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations, with additional designations possible in the future. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.